When the compile menu is hit

Runtime r = Runtime.getRuntime();
Process p = r.exec("javac test.java");
... see previous code

Use regex to parse the errors and put the cursor on the first error in the first file
Then each time a key is hit (I like F4) put the cursor on the NEXT error.

If you use JavaCompiler + 100
https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/javax/tools/JavaCompiler.html

If you compile fast in RAM + 400

